# davega.net — Desktop Metaphor Personal Website

> **Self-Maintaining**: Keep this file current as the codebase evolves. Update when conventions change, folders are added, or architecture decisions shift.

## Overview

Personal website at davega.net with a desktop metaphor UI. Visitors interact with draggable icons on a desktop surface; clicking an icon opens that section in a window (with minimize, enlarge, close controls). Content sections: Newsletter (articles), About, Photography, Contact. Mobile visitors see a "coming soon" placeholder. Layout detected by viewport width (768px breakpoint).

## Tech Stack

- React 19, TypeScript (strict), Vite, pnpm
- Tailwind CSS v4 (`@tailwindcss/vite` plugin, `@custom-variant dark` for dark mode)
- @dnd-kit v2 (`@dnd-kit/react`, `@dnd-kit/dom`) for drag-and-drop
- Deployed to GitHub Pages via Actions on push to main
- Build output: `./build` (not default `dist/`)

## Folder Structure

```
src/
├── desktop/              # Desktop metaphor shell
│   ├── background/       # Wallpaper/visual backdrop
│   ├── toolbar/          # Top bar with theme + layout toggles
│   ├── icon/             # Draggable section icons
│   ├── window/           # Window wrapper (title bar: minimize, enlarge, close)
│   ├── DesktopSurface.tsx # Root desktop component
│   └── index.ts          # Shell barrel export
├── mobile/               # Mobile layout (coming soon placeholder)
│   ├── ComingSoon.tsx
│   └── index.ts
├── sections/             # Content sections (co-located)
│   ├── about/
│   ├── contact/
│   ├── newsletter/
│   └── photography/
├── shared/               # Cross-cutting utilities, hooks, types
│   ├── hooks/
│   │   ├── use-theme.ts        # Theme state + system preference
│   │   └── use-device-layout.ts # Viewport detection + manual override
│   ├── types.ts          # Shared type definitions + SECTIONS constant
│   └── index.ts          # Barrel export
├── App.tsx               # Layout router (desktop vs mobile)
├── index.css             # Tailwind entry + theme variables + dark overrides
└── main.tsx              # Entry point
```

## Conventions

- **Folders**: kebab-case (`desktop/background/`, `sections/newsletter/`)
- **Components**: PascalCase (`Background.tsx`, `Window.tsx`)
- **Barrel exports**: Each folder has an `index.ts` for public API
- **Co-location**: All files for a component (code, styles, tests, assets) live in its folder
- **Styling**: Tailwind utility classes with CSS custom properties for theme tokens. Dark mode via `.dark` class on `<html>` and `dark:` Tailwind variant.
- **Hooks**: Custom hooks in `shared/hooks/` with `use-` prefix (kebab-case files)

## Architecture Decisions

- **Two layout modules** — `desktop/` and `mobile/` are sibling layout trees. Shared concerns (theme, device detection, types) live in `shared/`.
- **App.tsx is a layout router** — uses `useDeviceLayout()` to conditionally render DesktopSurface or ComingSoon.
- **Sections are pure content** — they render inside windows but have no knowledge of the desktop shell (icons, windows, drag behavior)
- **Desktop shell owns the chrome** — window title bar, icon drag, toolbar, and background are all under `src/desktop/`
- **Adding a new section** = add an entry to `SECTIONS` in `src/shared/types.ts`. No other folders need modification.
- **Theme is shared** — `useTheme()` hook manages `.dark` class on `<html>`. All components use `dark:` Tailwind classes. FOUC prevented by inline script in `index.html`.
- **Single-package project** — no pnpm workspaces or monorepo tooling

## Commands

```bash
pnpm dev        # Dev server on port 3000
pnpm build      # Type-check + Vite build to ./build
pnpm lint       # ESLint
pnpm preview    # Serve production build locally
```
